Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:52.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Villar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.84,0:02:14.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Duke Theo Cornaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.01,0:02:17.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Once again the time has come\Nfor me to offer you my Crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.55,0:02:22.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If there are no objections.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.18,0:02:26.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no one who would object to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.85,0:02:33.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Earl of Sistina, it is clear to us all by now that\Nyou're the right man to lead the Altirk Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.11,0:02:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, intend to pledge allegiance to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:38.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo, I'd like to serve you, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:44.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, I intend to forsake\Nthe Constance name
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.16,0:02:48.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and take my mother's family name,\N"Stelea" instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.12,0:02:49.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.54,0:02:52.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nowhere near the caliber\Nof my brother Villar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.84,0:02:56.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even on that day\Nthat we lost this castle to Milza,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.42,0:03:00.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,far from being an asset to him,\NI was only a liability.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:02.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:10.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who should succeed\Nthe Constance family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:11.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So as of today,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:14.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to become\Nthe head of the Constance family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.78,0:03:19.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.65,0:03:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With that in mind, you should\Nalso pledge fealty to Duke Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.62,0:03:26.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we combined our Crests,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.20,0:03:30.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't be enough\Nto rule over Altirk and Regalia, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.17,0:03:33.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as Sir Theo is in agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.55,0:03:36.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.30,0:03:50.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that my master, the Earl of Sistina,\NTheo Cornaro has become leader of the Treaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.73,0:03:55.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we're in agreement\Nto entrust your Crests to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.83,0:04:21.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I plan to carry on the legacy of\NEarl Villar Constance who died shielding us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:27.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sir Villar stayed true to the Union's resolution\Nto push for peace with the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.22,0:04:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I'd like us to strive for that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.68,0:04:34.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so in order to take a neutral position,\Nthe Altirk Treaty
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.15,0:04:37.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,will hereby break away from the Union!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:43.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we declare independence now,\Nit will rattle the Union even more,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.32,0:04:45.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and I don't see\Nthe Alliance agreeing to reconcile.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.28,0:04:49.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, wouldn't such a move\Nbenefit the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:52.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're still going to cooperate\Nwith the Union as we always have,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.08,0:04:54.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and we'll continue battling the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.46,0:04:59.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our goal is to ensure\Nthat the three factions strike a balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.50,0:05:01.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and bring the fighting to a standstill.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.76,0:05:04.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, there won't be anything\Nto negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:08.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I guess our only option\Nis to hope the Union comes through.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.43,0:05:11.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. If the Union doesn't make a move,\Nwe're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.68,0:05:16.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We might have defeated Prince Milza\Nand reclaimed Altirk,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.52,0:05:18.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but the Alliance is still as powerful as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.90,0:05:21.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, we have no time\Nto sit back and relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.99,0:05:22.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:27.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,why don't we celebrate our victories\Non the battlefield just for tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.64,0:06:32.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Seriously, I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.73,0:06:41.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.69,0:06:42.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sir Theo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.32,0:06:46.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}You still haven't gone to bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.11,0:06:47.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.90,0:06:50.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}You must be tired.\NPlease get some rest now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:52.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I'm planning to do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.91,0:06:56.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to talk to you\Nabout something first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.71,0:07:05.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Here you go.\N- Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.81,0:07:19.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations on becoming leader\Nof the Altirk Treaty, and a duke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:22.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone can see that I'm out of place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.65,0:07:24.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you seemed so comfortable in the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.15,0:07:27.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,During the banquet,\Nyou showed no signs of arrogance,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.69,0:07:31.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and was kind and considerate\Nas you interacted with the Lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.87,0:07:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were yourself, Sir Theo.\NI think that's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:37.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm relieved\Nthat they acknowledge me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.04,0:07:41.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your popularity among the soldiers\Nand the people was overwhelming, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:46.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All you had to do was show yourself,\Nand everyone would start cheering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:49.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though so many soldiers lost\Ntheir lives under my watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.51,0:07:53.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and even cost the civilians\Nso many lives, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:54.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}To be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.18,0:07:56.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}it pains my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:07:59.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ever forget that feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.23,0:08:03.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and try to rule in a way\Nthat benefits your people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.77,0:08:06.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. I'll never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.36,0:08:09.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But my final dream hasn't changed\Nafter all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.03,0:08:13.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To return to my homeland, Marza,\Nand to bring happiness to my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.62,0:08:14.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.78,0:08:19.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, actually, there's just one thing\Nthat's changed since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.71,0:08:22.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.54,0:08:23.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's my final dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.54,0:08:26.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I go back to Marza,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.05,0:08:28.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to be by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:33.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I first met you, Sir Theo,\NI pledged my eternal loyalty to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:36.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Needless to say, I intend to serve you\Nfor the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.64,0:08:40.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'm not getting through to you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.77,0:08:49.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Two people who love each other\Nshould be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.49,0:08:54.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}And I don't just mean\NSir Alexis and Lady Marrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.16,0:08:57.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}S-Since this is a crucial topic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.58,0:09:00.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}please be specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:05.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I return to Marza,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.13,0:09:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you by my side\Nnot as my contracted mage
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.38,0:09:11.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but as my queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.72,0:09:15.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I tried not to think about that too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.55,0:09:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just getting to have the same dream as you,\NSir Theo, makes me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:26.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As does being alone with you\Nand being treated so kindly, like now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.23,0:09:29.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, with your status now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you could find any number\Nof lovely women to be your queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.57,0:09:35.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even think of anyone but you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.28,0:09:38.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to make that clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.62,0:09:49.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then,\Nstarting now, I will be your queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But do you mind if we keep it private\Nuntil after we've achieved our goals?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.88,0:09:56.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.55,0:09:59.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The important thing\Nis how we feel about each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.76,0:10:01.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.35,0:10:03.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have a favor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:05.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.15,0:10:10.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't die before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.15,0:10:18.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The world is overrun with Chaos,\Nand we live in a turbulent age.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.37,0:10:23.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a Lord, and I'm about to go into battle\Nwith a powerful enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.37,0:10:25.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I still want you to promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:28.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if I can't keep that promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.58,0:10:30.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll die, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.42,0:10:33.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's a grave responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.59,0:10:39.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro has been named\Nleader of the Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:44.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}So the Treaty's solidarity is now unshakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.18,0:10:48.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How is the Earl of Le Couleurs?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:51.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As he was close to the Earl of Altirk,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.86,0:10:54.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's highly likely\Nthat he'll join forces with the Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is a formidable opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.40,0:11:01.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to avoid any invasions by him\Nand the Treaty members, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:05.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How are those negotiations going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.50,0:11:08.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've received word that they're going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:10.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell them\Nto set it in motion immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.04,0:11:11.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.67,0:11:14.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we can take down\Nthe Earl of Le Couleurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:17.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can drastically undermine\Nthe Treaty's military power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:18.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll finish this off at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:29.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see you're growing steadily.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.73,0:11:30.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Priscilla!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.98,0:11:31.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.19,0:11:34.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.40,0:11:39.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:42.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.53,0:11:49.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pope Leone of the Order of the Crest\Nproclaimed himself to be the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.50,0:11:50.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.83,0:11:53.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the true Holy Grail, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:58.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was born with a Crest in my possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:03.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it's true\Nthat my Crest is shaped like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.60,0:12:07.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father always said\Nthat I was the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:08.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}For that reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.35,0:12:14.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}some of our followers do call me\Nthe "Holy Grail of Farnese."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.94,0:12:16.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:20.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's the founder of the Order of the Crest,\NErnest Farnese, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.20,0:12:21.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.41,0:12:25.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is the Holy Grail anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:30.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Order of the Crest preaches that by gathering\Nall of the world's Crests into the Holy Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.46,0:12:34.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you can summon a god to eliminate the Chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:35.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.13,0:12:38.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it's the same thing\Nas the Holy Crest, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.42,0:12:41.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're known as the Holy Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.59,0:12:44.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you're probably a hindrance to the pope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:48.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that man sees me that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.89,0:12:52.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The pope might try to harm you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:12:53.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.48,0:12:56.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You be careful, too, Sir Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.77,0:13:00.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he's declared himself to be the Holy Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:02.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then he's voicing his intent\Nto gather all the Crests.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.74,0:13:06.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, I think it's highly probable\Nthat he's targeting your Crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.16,0:13:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.45,0:13:12.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Siluca, how do you feel\Nabout the Order of the Crest now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.87,0:13:15.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To me, both the order's doctrines\Nand the Holy Grail
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.08,0:13:19.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,just seem like myths\Ncreated for convenience's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.30,0:13:26.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I might have become the Treaty's leader\Nthanks to the guidance of the one god.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:29.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you worked hard\Nfor it, Sir Theo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.97,0:13:34.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you do, please don't\Noffer your Crest to the Order of the Crest!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:35.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.81,0:13:38.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it turns out that I can save you\Nand the others with this Crest,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.19,0:13:41.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll offer it without a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.49,0:13:44.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Siluca, I have a report for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.95,0:13:55.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I received a report that\Nthe Earl of Le Couleurs, Sir Croute Gallas,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.54,0:14:02.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,met a heroic death\Nwhile battling the Waldlind forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.59,0:14:05.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Croute...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:09.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before our reinforcements could reach them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.35,0:14:14.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he was betrayed by the mercenaries\Nsent by Lord Dawson, and then he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.27,0:14:16.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards,\Nwhat has Lord Dawson been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.73,0:14:19.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that he was welcomed\Ninto the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:22.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So Lord Dawson did have\Na secret agreement in place all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.19,0:14:24.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It appears so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:27.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's gathered\Nthe most devout Lords of the Alliance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:29.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and called on them to pledge\Ntheir allegiance to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.20,0:14:32.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How did the Lords he summoned react?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.66,0:14:35.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At this time, none of them\Nseem to have complied.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.71,0:14:36.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.25,0:14:40.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now that the Union has lost\Nthe Earl of Le Couleurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.42,0:14:42.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,things are looking even bleaker, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:45.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For things not to turn out the way we want...\NThat's how it's always been.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:47.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The important thing\Nis how we're going to adjust.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:50.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have an idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.55,0:14:52.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I wouldn't go so far\Nas to call it an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.89,0:14:54.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go to Jalucia together?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:57.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.27,0:15:00.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Treaty has broken away from the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:04.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In their eyes,\Nwe might just be a bunch of traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.82,0:15:08.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As far as that goes,\Nwe'll have to believe in Sir Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.07,0:15:12.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all this distressing news,\Nthe Earl of Jalucia must be despondent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.45,0:15:15.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're his friend, Sir Theo,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.54,0:15:17.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,please do what you can to cheer him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:19.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cheer him up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.54,0:15:21.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}With the Earl of Le Couleurs dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:25.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}only Sir Alexis can save the Union\Nfrom this crisis now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.30,0:15:29.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}If he should rise up,\Nthe other Lords are sure to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are those...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...ironclad warships.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.10,0:15:43.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think they were included in the reward\Nfor attaining the rank of viscount.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:47.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that the previous archduke used\Nhis surplus court ranks to procure them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.11,0:15:51.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But apparently they're slow in the water,\Nand have no practical use to speak of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.28,0:15:54.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since they're warships\Nunable to fight the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.95,0:15:57.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the locals call them "peace ships."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:16:00.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Though they do look intimidating\Nbeyond belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:03.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.75,0:16:07.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alexis says\Nthat he will be delighted to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:09.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:15.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard the rumors\Nabout your achievements!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.18,0:16:19.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was like hearing the legend\Nof the First Lord, Leon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.60,0:16:22.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I owe it all to my comrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.10,0:16:24.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,starting with Siluca here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.48,0:16:28.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you've been named\Nleader of the Altirk Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.82,0:16:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.11,0:16:32.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you've broken away from the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.11,0:16:35.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any way that you'd reconsider?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.12,0:16:38.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because there's no one\NI can rely on but you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.95,0:16:42.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I even wish you'd take over\Nas leader of the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:45.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.92,0:16:49.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because what I want\Nis for the Union and Alliance to reconcile.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.47,0:16:51.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reconcile?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:55.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't been so insistent\Nabout reconciling,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.60,0:16:57.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we wouldn't have lost the Earl of Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:17:01.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That day, if only I'd chosen\Nto go to war against the Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.64,0:17:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}the Union wouldn't be in this position now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.48,0:17:07.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That might be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.98,0:17:11.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}But surely you've lost something\Neven more precious, Sir Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.32,0:17:14.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Marrine...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.62,0:17:18.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Union ends up\Ndefeating the Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:23.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure a world without Lady Marrine\Nwould hold no purpose for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.33,0:17:25.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.25,0:17:27.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I sought peace with the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.59,0:17:30.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it was different for Marrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.43,0:17:39.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's because Lady Marrine believes\Nshe must create the Emperor's Holy Crest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:43.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by unifying the Crests\Nthrough military might.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.77,0:17:46.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the fact that the Crests\Nwould've been unified eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:49.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if she and I had married?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because there are people\Nwho don't want that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:54.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what triggered that tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.70,0:17:55.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:17:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everything changed after that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.87,0:18:03.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so I want to negate that tragedy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:06.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to restore the world\Nthat existed before that incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.25,0:18:10.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Needless to say,\Nthat's what I wish for, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.13,0:18:13.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I no longer feel that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.05,0:18:15.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:21.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We need the Union, the Alliance, and the Treaty\Nto strike a military balance for that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.47,0:18:24.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Union isn't capable of...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.48,0:18:25.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.69,0:18:29.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Union nations are all affluent,\Nand since they haven't been at war,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.94,0:18:32.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,their human resources\Nhaven't been depleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.44,0:18:36.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Alliance is surely suffering the effects\Nof having fought in consecutive battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.53,0:18:38.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you were to rise up, Sir Alexis, I'm sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.53,0:18:42.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.12,0:18:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even to save Lady Marrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.21,0:18:51.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Save her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.34,0:18:54.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:58.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she unifies the Crests\Nby military force, and becomes emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.55,0:19:00.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,she can never be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.39,0:19:02.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.97,0:19:05.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Marrine is acting of her own volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.10,0:19:11.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}She is only suppressing her feelings\Nto fulfill her duty as the leader of the Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.69,0:19:14.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}But I don't find that commendable at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.36,0:19:19.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because if she's not being true to her heart,\Nthere's no point to anything she accomplishes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:25.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To me, it's unforgivable that she's continuing\Nto fight while stifling her soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.29,0:19:29.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the fact that she's in love with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.67,0:19:31.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:32.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.46,0:19:36.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine is still in love with you even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.47,0:19:41.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.27,0:19:48.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one\Nwho can stop Lady Marrine but you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.52,0:19:54.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've made up my mind.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:57.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What have you decided?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.57,0:20:00.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll be your queen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.68,0:20:32.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alexis, where are you heading?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.90,0:20:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm setting off to attack Lord Dawson!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.36,0:20:40.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alexis!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.95,0:20:44.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to mobilize immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.45,0:20:50.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alexis has decided to rise up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.04,0:20:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of late in the game,\Nbut this should be interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:55.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's all join the rampage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.79,0:20:58.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's follow Sir Alexis's lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That Earl of Le Couleurs\Nwas hardly a worthy opponent, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.31,0:21:08.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.35,0:21:15.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Even that Doucet moppet, the Union is a collection\Nof spineless fools who lack foresight, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.56,0:21:17.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're absolutely right, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.24,0:21:25.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon the intrusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.45,0:21:29.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A massive force led by the Earl of Jalucia\Nis advancing towards this castle right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.54,0:21:30.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:51.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If the Alliance were to win,\Nand Marrine became emperor,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.68,0:21:53.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought the world would become\Na better place.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.44,0:21:57.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But if it means that she'll be hurt...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.03,0:22:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.03,0:22:04.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,LEADER
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.95,0:23:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 19\NTHE AWAKENING OF A NOBLE
